{'topic': 'Seating Arrangements (Circular)', 'question': 'Six friends A, B, C, D, E, and F sit around a round table. The following conditions hold:
(i) B sits immediately clockwise of A;
(ii) D is directly opposite B;
(iii) E sits two places counter‑clockwise from D;
(iv) F sits immediately counter‑clockwise of the person who is opposite C;
(v) A is not opposite E.
Who is sitting directly opposite A?', 'choices': ['A) B', 'B) D', 'C) C', 'D) F'], 'answer': 'C', 'explanation': 'Fix A at any seat. Then B is clockwise of A, D opposite B, and E two seats CCW from D, leaving seats for C and F. Only placement satisfying (iv) and (v) is C opposite A and F next to the opposite of C. Hence C sits opposite A.'}
